<h1><font color="#5C8526">Milestone : Possible Changes</font></h1>
<ul><li><h2>When we add a new functional dependency, X --&gt; Y, after the decomposition, we will have two tables containing the attribute X, while Y may appear only once.  </h2></li>
<li><h2>Therefore, if a query contains a predicate on the attribute X then, we need add a <b>JOIN</b> operation to the query. </h2></li>
</ul></body>
